msgid "Now when the client emits a message in the following way:"
msgstr "Now when the client emits a message in the following way:"

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:108
msgid ""
"The ``handleEvent()`` method will be executed. In order to listen to "
"messages emitted from within the above handler, the client has to attach "
"a corresponding acknowledgment listener:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:117
msgid "Multiple responses"
msgstr "Multiple responses"

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:119
msgid ""
"The acknowledgment is dispatched only once. Furthermore, it is not "
"supported by native WebSockets implementation. To solve this limitation, "
"you may return an object which consist of two properties. The ``event`` "
"which is a name of the emitted event and the ``data`` that has to be "
"forwarded to the client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:142
msgid ""
"info **Hint** The ``WsResponse`` interface is imported from "
"``@nestjs/websockets`` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:145
msgid ""
"In order to listen for the incoming response(s), the client has to apply "
"another event listener."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:153
msgid "Asynchronous responses"
msgstr "Asynchronous responses"

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:155
msgid ""
"Each message handler can be either synchronous or **asynchronous** "
"(``async``), thereby you’re able to return the ``Promise``. Moreover, you"
" can return the `Observable <https://github.com/reactivex/rxjs>`__, which"
" means that you can return multiple values (they will be emitted until "
"the stream is completed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/gateways.rst:184
msgid ""
"The above message handler will respond **3 times** (sequentially, with "
"each item from the ``response`` array)."
msgstr ""

